Revenue increased by 5%, to $12.3 billion.
Six analysts surveyed, Zacks expected $12.23 billion.
FedEx has suffered in recent years from the downturn in the sector of urgent international transportation, which has led to a lack of growth in gross revenue in its express shipping division.
However, the boom in online shopping has dramatically improved the results at FedEx Ground.
